Product Requirements Document: Hartz AI Website

1. Project Overview

Hartz AI is a London-based AI consultancy and training lab focused on empowering UK SMEs. The goal of this project is to build a high-conversion, atmospheric landing page that mirrors the "Digital Lab" aesthetic of Google DeepMind.

2. Core Aesthetic & Brand Guidelines

Refer to the "Digital Lab" Design Brief for full visual specs.

Colors: #FFFFFF (Primary Background), #4A90E2 (Hartz Blue Accent), #0A0A0A (Primary Text).

Typography: Inter (Global Font). Headlines must be ExtraBold with tight tracking (-0.05em).

Vibe: Expansive whitespace, "bioluminescent" blue glows, technical hairlines (0.5px), and a subtle grain texture.

3. Technical Requirements

Framework: Single-file architecture (HTML5, Tailwind CSS, Vanilla JavaScript).

Responsiveness: Fully fluid layout (Mobile, Tablet, Desktop). No fixed pixel widths.

Interactivity: - Smooth scroll behavior.

CSS/JS animations for "hero orbs" and bento card hovers.

Glassmorphism effects for navigation.

4. Functional Requirements & Page Structure

4.1. Navigation (Mega-Menu)

Component: Fixed "Glass" navbar with 20px+ backdrop-blur.

Structure:

Logo: "HARTZ" (Inter Bold) + Blue Circle "AI".

Menu Items: Training (Mega-menu with Academy/Workshops/Resources), Consultancy (Mega-menu with Audit/Fractional CAIO/Advisory), Case Studies, About.

CTA: "Book Discovery Call" button (Primary Black).

4.2. Hero Section (The Hook)

Visual: Background "hero orb" with slow floating animation.

Copy: - Primary Headline: "Solving intelligence to advance humanity."

Sub-headline: "Practical AI for a smarter workforce."

Stats: Integrated counter/visuals for: 500+ Trained, 90% Confidence Increase, 40% Time Saved.

4.3. Phased Roadmap (Process)

Layout: 4-column grid (Audit -> Roadmap -> Delivery -> Independence).

Interactive: Hover states that highlight the current phaseâ€™s progress bar.

4.4. Service Bento Grid

Cards:

Hartz AI Academy (Main Feature - 8/12 width).

Fractional CAIO (4/12 width).

AI Readiness Audit (4/12 width).

Bespoke AI Solutions (8/12 width).

Style: 32px corner radius, thin borders, abstract SVG line-art visuals.

4.5. Trust & Social Proof

Industry Tags: Clean, grayscale tags (UK Sport, Charities, Education, etc.).

Testimonials: Large-format quotes with circular headshots and professional titles.

4.6. FAQ & Final CTA

FAQ: Standard accordion with "Plus/Minus" toggles.

Final CTA: A high-impact, dark-mode card ("A gentle first step into AI") with a centralized button.

5. Implementation Notes for AI

Single File: All HTML, CSS (via Tailwind CDN), and JS must reside in index.html.

Iconography: Use Lucide icons or Inline SVGs. No external image dependencies.

Accessibility: High contrast ratios for text and ARIA labels for interactive elements.